Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Where to solo 36+</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I have been trying to quad kite the spectres in the Oasis and there are just too many to kite.  I have successfully killed maybe 1 or 2 out of 4 pulls everytime at lvl 36 and I have to zone to clear the aggro because I was OOM.  I have a problem with the spectres don't want to be in a bundle and I have to recast BoF 2 or 3 times to make sure the BoF stick.  So far after many close encounter with death.  I don't know if I want to continue kiting the spectres.  They even cast lifetap even when they are running to get me.  If one of them are casting, they are not in a close group for the AOE spell.  Any suggestion?  New tactics?  New places to go?<br>
<br>
Cueene<br>
36th Circle<br>
Psychic Venom<br>
Erollisi Marr</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cueene>Cueene</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/15/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>12:17:35 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Where to solo 36+</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">There is about 6 spectres whenever I pull full spawn.<br>
<br>
Cueene<br>
36th Circle<br>
Psychic Venom<br>
Erollisi Marr</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#33333><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udrombacgunn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Drombac Gunn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/15/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>9:05:35 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">suggestion</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">try hill giants in rathe...good xp, GREAT money<br>
<br>
you wont be quad kiting them, but at that level..quad kiting is stil a bit too dangerous to be well worth it. as you found out, not only do you need skill and and the right spells..you need the right mob. if spectres were any good for quading at all...there would druids doin it 24/7... the best time fo quad kiting is 51+ with pillar spells..fast casting low cost 4 mob spells..seemingly designed for it.<br>
<br>
but if you simply must do it....head over to Kunark or velious and try experimenting there...you should find plenty of wide open space in either place, few poeple and lots of mobs to kite<br>
<br>
the poeple factor is a big one here, for while you inocently enough zoned to avoid being eaten by nasty spectres. more than likely more than one noob fell victim to its clutches as it lost you and went rampaging across the zone in rage.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/16/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>12:12:48 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Where to solo 36+</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">at your level you should head for Eastern Wastes. You can probably quad walrus, if not, you can take walrus and ulthork hunters solo. By 39 you should easily be quading hunters and then switching to warriors around 40-41. It starts to green out at 43, but if the zone is empty you can still quad blues here. There are also a ton of frost giants in the area you can kite for loot and exp.</font><P><span style="font-size: 18px; font-famliy: arial"><b>Wandor Kilbringer<br>Wizard of the 43rd Conclave<br>Vini, Vidi, Nuki</b></span><br>
<i>I came, I saw, I nuked the crap out of everything in sight!</i><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#33333><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utralantuebor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tralan Tuebor</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ancientfellowship.org/images/AF.gif BORDER=0></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/25/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5:46:26 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.ancientfellowship.org/images/tralan53.jpg hieght=216 width=115></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Where to solo 36+</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I have had some luck with the Drakkel Dire Wolves in GD.  Bonds of Force sticks to them fairly well, and as long as each one has been Temp Fluxed, they take full damage (205 @ 35).  Normally I'll take 3, just in case I get resists and need the mana to take out a stray.<br>
<br>
The wolves are slow and they help build Dwarf and Dragon Faction.  You only have to be careful of the giants.  They are fast, hit hard, and have way too many HP to solo effectively.  On ONE Frost Giant Scout (white to me @ 35) I burned all of my mana, used Harvest, AND had Clarity to put him down alone.<br>
<br>
IMO, giants just aren't worth soloing if they are even or higher con.  Stick with wolves in GD.<br>
<br>
<br>
Brindar<br>
Level 35 Wizard<br>
